    {
      "id": 211,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "To fly / To lift",
      "hw": "اُڑنا",
      "s": "«نَسَفَ» to scatter or destroy something (3 verses: 20:97-20:105-77:10)",
      "d": "«نَسَفَ الْحَبَّ» means to thresh grain with a winnowing shovel, and «مِنْسَف» is a winnowing shovel or sieve used to clean grain. «نَسَفَ الرِّیْح» means for the wind to uproot something from its base and scatter it (as in the dictionary) and also means to crush mountains and scatter them in the wind (as in the commentary).\nFor example: The Quran states:\n«وَ یَسۡئَلُوۡنَکَ عَنِ الۡجِبَالِ فَقُلۡ یَنۡسِفُہَا رَبِّیۡ  نَسۡفًا» (20/105)\nTranslation: And they ask you about the mountains, so say, 'My Lord will scatter them utterly.'"
    },
