  "41": [
    {
      "id": 225,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "moderation",
      "hw": "اعتدال",
      "s": "«قَصْد» to avoid excess and deficiency in an action and choose the path of moderation (3 verses: 9:42-16:9-31:19)",
      "d": "«قَصْد» and «اِقْتِصَاد» both mean to choose the middle path while avoiding excess and deficiency. The only difference is that «اِقْتِصَاد» is generally used in the context of expenditures and spending, whereas «قَصْد» is a general term.\nFor example, the Quran says: «وَ اقۡصِدۡ فِیۡ  مَشۡیِکَ» (31/19) Translation: Be moderate in your walking.\nAnd «قَصْدُ السَّبِیۡل» means to choose the middle and moderate path while avoiding excess and deficiency, and this is the only path that can be straight. While all other paths are inclined towards excess or deficiency or are crooked.\nFor example, the Quran says: «وَعَلَی اللّٰہِ قَصۡدُ السَّبِیۡلِ وَ مِنۡہَا جَآئِرٌ» (16/9) Translation: And upon Allah is the straight path (Uthmani), and all other paths are crooked.\nNote: (Excess and deficiency: less and more, unbalanced state, less and more, a little and a lot. Excess: means to exceed the limit, to exaggerate in describing someone's status. The Quran has described it as 'غُلُوّ' and in Arabic it is also called 'تَطرُّف' (Excessiveness). Deficiency: means to decrease in someone's status and lower them from their rank.)"
    },
    {
      "id": 226,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "moderation",
      "hw": "اعتدال",
      "s": "«وَسْط» is used for the middle of a single thing or the middle thing among two or more things (2 verses: 2:143-2:238)",
      "d": "«وَسْط» is the middle of a single thing or the middle among two or more things. It seems this word is stronger than «قصد» and «وَسَطَ» means in every matter to choose the middle and moderate path.\nFor example, the Quran says: «وَ کَذٰلِکَ جَعَلۡنٰکُمۡ اُمَّۃً وَّسَطًا لِّتَکُوۡنُوۡا شُہَدَآءَ عَلَی النَّاسِ» (2/143) Translation: And thus we have made you a moderate nation so that you may be witnesses over the people."
    },
    {
      "id": 227,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Moderation",
      "hw": "اعتدال",
      "s": "«تَقْوِیْم» to maintain moderation from every aspect in one thing (1 verse: 95:4)",
      "d": "«تَقْوِیْم» relates to one thing such that all aspects of excess and deficiency are removed from it. And it becomes balanced, proportionate, and moderate. In it, there is no sway, tilt, or crookedness (Faq l 174). «قَوْمُ الشَّیءِ» means to determine and adjust a thing. From this, «تَقْوِیْمُ الْبَدَان» is derived because in it the length and width of cities are described, and «قَوَّمَ دَرْأَہٗ» means to straighten crookedness (Munjid).\nFor example: In the Quran it is said: «لَقَدۡ خَلَقۡنَا الۡاِنۡسَانَ فِیۡۤ  اَحۡسَنِ تَقۡوِیۡمٍ» (95/4) Translation: Indeed, We have created man in the best stature."
    },
    {
      "id": 4000,
      "hw": "break",
      "s": "«حَنِثَ» to break an oath (2 verses: 38:44-56:46)",
      "d": "",
      "h": "To break an oath"
    },
    {
