  "42": [
    {
      "id": 229,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Record of deeds",
      "hw": "اعمال",
      "s": "«کِتَاب» every written or recorded thing is called a book. (232 verses: 2:2-2:44-2:53-2:78-2:79-2:85-2:87-2:89-2:101-2:105-2:109-2:113-2:121-2:129-2:144-2:145-2:146-2:151-2:159-2:174-2:176-2:177-2:213-2:231-2:235-3:3-3:7-3:19-3:20-3:23-3:48-3:64-3:65-3:69-3:70-3:71-3:72-3:75-3:78-3:79-3:81-3:98-3:99-3:100-3:110-3:113-3:119-3:145-3:164-3:184-3:186-3:187-3:199-4:24-4:44-4:47-4:51-4:54-4:103-4:105-4:113-4:123-4:127-4:131-4:136-4:140-4:153-4:159-4:171-5:5-5:15-5:19-5:44-5:48-5:57-5:59-5:65-5:68-5:77-5:110-6:7-6:20-6:38-6:59-6:89-6:91-6:92-6:114-6:154-6:155-6:156-6:157-7:2-7:37-7:52-7:169-7:170-7:196-8:68-8:75-9:29-9:36-10:1-10:37-10:61-10:94-11:1-11:6-11:17-11:110-12:1-13:1-13:36-13:38-13:39-13:43-14:1-15:1-15:4-16:64-16:89-17:2-17:4-17:13-17:14-17:58-17:71-17:93-18:1-18:27-18:49-19:12-19:16-19:30-19:41-19:51-19:54-19:56-20:52-21:10-22:8-22:70-23:49-23:62-24:33-25:35-26:2-27:1-27:28-27:29-27:40-27:75-28:2-28:43-28:49-28:52-28:86-29:27-29:45-29:46-29:47-29:48-29:51-30:56-31:2-31:20-32:2-32:23-33:6-33:26-34:3-35:11-35:25-35:29-35:31-35:32-35:40-37:117-37:157-38:29-39:1-39:2-39:23-39:41-39:69-40:2-40:53-40:70-41:3-41:41-41:45-42:14-42:15-42:17-42:52-43:2-43:4-43:21-44:2-45:2-45:16-45:28-45:29-46:2-46:4-46:12-46:30-50:4-52:2-56:78-57:16-57:22-57:25-57:26-57:29-59:2-59:11-62:2-68:37-69:19-69:25-74:31-78:29-83:7-83:9-83:18-83:20-84:7-84:10-98:1-98:4-98:6)",
      "d": "«کَتَب» means to write, and every type of writing, whether small or large, script or newspaper, any thick book, all fall under this word. And humans' deeds are also being written continuously by the noble scribes. Therefore, the record of deeds is called a writing in this sense.\nFor example: In the Quran it is:\n«وَ نُخۡرِجُ لَہٗ یَوۡمَ الۡقِیٰمَۃِ کِتٰبًا  یَّلۡقٰىہُ  مَنۡشُوۡرًا» (17/13)\nTranslation: And We will bring forth for him on the Day of Resurrection a book which he will find wide open."
    },
    {
      "id": 230,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Record of Deeds",
      "hw": "اعمال",
      "s": "«قِطّ» The register in which the account is written. (1 verse: 38:16)",
      "d": "«قِطّ» meaning the register of account. Command. Writing of reckoning. Deeds (manuscript. maf) The Record of Deeds is called «قِطّ» in the Quran because this very writing will be the basis for the reckoning of humans.\nFor example, in the Quran it is:\n«وَ قَالُوۡا رَبَّنَا عَجِّلۡ  لَّنَا قِطَّنَا قَبۡلَ یَوۡمِ  الۡحِسَابِ» (38/16)\nTranslation: And they say: O our Lord! Hasten for us our record before the Day of Reckoning."
    },
    {
      "id": 231,
      "a": "ا",
      "h": "Record of deeds",
      "hw": "اعمال",
      "s": "«صُحُف» to collect written papers in the form of a book (8 verses: 20:133-53:36-74:52-80:13-81:10-87:18-87:19-98:2)",
      "d": "«صُحُف» (singular) means a spread-out thing and anything on which something is written (maf). Sahifah means a written paper, leaf. And «صِحَافَۃ» means journalism, and «اَصْحَفَ» means to collect scrolls or written leaves into the form of a book. And «مُصْحَف» means a book, and its plural is «مَصَاحِف» (manjad). And the record of deeds is called Sahifah from this perspective because it will be in the form of large spread-out pages.\nFor example: In the Quran it is:\n«وَاِذَا الصُّحُفُ نُشِرَتۡ» (81/10)\nTranslation: And when the (deeds') scrolls are spread open."
    },
    {
